Cyp4f13
However, CYP4F enzymes are likely more relevant, as over- expression of the mouse orthologue Cyp4f13 but not of Cyp4a10 increased the formation of 1-deoxySL downstream products. Generally, mice express a broader spectrum of Cyp4a and Cyp4f isoenzymes than humans and therefore also seem to have a higher capacity to metabolize 1-deoxySLs. This might explain why 1-deoxySL plasma levels are lower in mice compared to humans, which should be considered when studying the physiological and pathophysiological effects of 1-deoxySL in rodent models.
